HEADWORD: Kefir grains
<hw>Kefir grains</hw>. <def>Small hard yellowish aggregations found in
the Caucasus region, and containing various yeasts and bacteria. They
are used as a ferment in preparing kefir.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

